artifact_name: cup type a(?); cup type c(?)
Description: Rim sherd of Attic black-figured pottery cup of type A or C; interior: reserved band at rim, glazed black below; top of rim glazed; exterior: dilute band around rim; below, black-figure decoration (partly fired reddish) consisting of facing figures (part of head of male standing, to right with added red dot in hair and possibly hand raised; head, shoulders, chest and left upper arm of probable female standing to left with two red dots in hair and faded added white bands, perhaps of nebris); vines in field.
Curator's comments: According to Venit, the sherd is by the same hand as British Museum 1965, 0930.780.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 450, no. B750)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0640) (Phase 1)
